data.description: Are you looking for an urban homestead with plenty of space, then look no further. Tucked away from traffic on a quiet cul-de-sac street in one of Greenville's oldest and most sought-after neighborhoods, Westcliffe. This large brick ranch has plenty of space and possibilities. With three bedrooms upstairs and three downstairs, there is space for everyone. Enjoy minimal maintenance with the laminate flooring throughout the house. The kitchen  has been updated with new flooring and the basement features new flooring throughout.  As you walk up the steps to the front porch which features a wrought-iron railing, you have a nice landing area to great guests.  Upon entering through the front door, you are presented with a bright and open living room. The sunroom which is just off the living room provides warm natural sunlight to brighten your day.  Enjoy ceiling fans throughout the home.  The sunroom provides a peaceful area to relax with plenty of new double-hung windows. This home features a generous amount of storage with numerous closets. When you want to head outside, you can relax on the private back porch overlooking the backyard.  With over a half-acre of land, there are plenty of opportunities for a garden.  There are already numerous fruit trees on the property.  The backyard has been terraced to maximize usable space providing a perfect area for a possible garden or outdoor area to enjoy.  The shed out back is large enough for your garden equipment. If you have pets, there are several fenced in areas for your animals to enjoy. The two-car garage also has lots of storage options in the workshop. The extra concrete pad offers plenty of parking area.? The location is wonderful with quick access to Saluda Lake, Downtown Travelers Rest,  Swamp Rabbit Trail, Cherrydale Point and only 10 minutes to  Downtown Greenville.
